Boris Chertok's memoir "Rockets and People" details his experiences over 60 years working on Soviet rocket and space programs, from early work collecting German technology after World War II to developing intercontinental ballistic missiles and launching the first human into space. The book provides first-hand insights into major milestones and challenges faced by the Soviet space program during the Cold War space race with the United States.
